-That and buy a Stair Master.

05:55.781 --> 05:57.413
-New Year's resolution?
-Yeah.

05:57.415 --> 05:58.447
It's like, October, Noah.

06:00.884 --> 06:02.216
Time flies.

06:02.218 --> 06:03.350
What have you
been doing though,

06:03.718 --> 06:05.251
other than planning the
reunion for three years?

06:05.253 --> 06:07.253
Well, uh, I am in real estate.

06:07.255 --> 06:08.487
Real estate!

06:08.855 --> 06:10.355
Yeah, yeah, let me
give you a card, you know.

06:11.690 --> 06:14.258
Of course, in this market you
can't give shit away, but...

06:14.260 --> 06:16.260
Is that your sales pitch?

06:16.262 --> 06:17.527
'Cause you got me.

06:18.028 --> 06:20.029
I hear you're gettin'
married Zach, congrats.

06:20.031 --> 06:21.363
Man, I got some great listings,

06:21.564 --> 06:22.363
great neighborhoods
for starting a family,

06:22.365 --> 06:23.497
that kinda thing.

06:23.898 --> 06:25.531
Yeah, I'm good, Noah.

06:26.566 --> 06:28.600
So what about you,
you got a girl, or...?

06:28.602 --> 06:29.634
You know, I do actually.

06:29.636 --> 06:30.801
Yeah? Oh, good.

06:31.402 --> 06:32.769
Yeah, yeah, yeah, it's getting
pretty serious actually.

06:32.771 --> 06:33.770
It's true what
they say, you know,

06:33.772 --> 06:35.772
there's someone out there
for everyone, even him.

06:36.908 --> 06:38.274
Even you, even you!

06:38.742 --> 06:40.008
Even you, come on!

06:40.275 --> 06:41.441
I feel like we're in
high school right now.

06:41.443 --> 06:42.875
Right now, at this moment.

06:44.777 --> 06:46.144
I bet your rich
daddy's gonna throw you

06:46.146 --> 06:47.311
one hell of a wedding.

06:47.712 --> 06:49.145
Well, uh...

06:49.479 --> 06:52.013
He passed, actually,
uh, blood clots.

06:52.247 --> 06:53.247
Sorry to hear that.

06:53.249 --> 06:54.414
That sucks, man, sorry.

06:54.416 --> 06:55.615
Thanks guys, thank you, yeah.

06:56.550 --> 06:57.650
Yeah.

06:58.118 --> 06:59.485
And he was worth a lot
of money, your father.

07:00.320 --> 07:01.720
You know, I mean
dealing with lawyers

07:01.722 --> 07:02.854
and the estate,
that's a big headache.

07:03.155 --> 07:04.455
You know, you're spot on about

07:04.656 --> 07:06.223
the real estate market,
I say the same thing

07:06.225 --> 07:07.557
to all my clients when
they come in, I say,

07:07.559 --> 07:08.991
"Until things turn around,

07:08.993 --> 07:10.993
avoid it
like the fuckin' plague."

07:11.427 --> 07:13.928
The smart money right now
is in portfolio management.

07:13.930 --> 07:15.496
-Is that right?
-I want you to take my card.

07:15.498 --> 07:17.231
Look at that.
Oh, man, that is a card.

07:17.233 --> 07:18.465
I want you to call me.

07:18.632 --> 07:19.832
Well, thanks, man,
I appreciate that.

07:19.834 --> 07:21.633
-You gonna call me?
-Sure.

07:21.635 --> 07:22.900
All right, I'm gonna
get outta here.

07:22.902 --> 07:24.234
Oh.
I got another round coming.

07:24.236 --> 07:25.635
I'm hydrated, I gotta go.

07:25.637 --> 07:27.737
Listen, if you, uh,
if you don't want

07:27.739 --> 07:29.972
any more to drink,
you know maybe umm,

07:30.807 --> 07:33.341
you guys wanna smoke outside?
A little four-twenty?

07:41.683 --> 07:43.116
Truth is, the
most prevalent thing

07:43.118 --> 07:44.984
that came out of
a day like today is:

07:44.986 --> 07:47.152
at any moment,
that could have been

07:47.154 --> 07:49.020
any one of us in that pine box.

07:49.788 --> 07:50.854
Yeah, man.

07:51.622 --> 07:53.489
That's why you have
to live in the moment.

07:53.957 --> 07:56.591
Like that preacher said, if the
opportunity presents itself,

07:58.093 --> 07:59.593
do not hesitate.

08:00.828 --> 08:02.295
Amen to that, my brother.

08:03.665 --> 08:05.364
Hey, you guys ever
hear of Bidexco?

08:05.832 --> 08:06.998
Bidexco?

08:07.299 --> 08:09.333
Yeah, it's a
pharmaceutical company,

08:09.335 --> 08:11.168
small startup, some
guys at my firm,

08:11.170 --> 08:12.502
we helped them raise capital.

08:12.504 --> 08:14.270
Why are you asking
about Bidexco?

08:14.272 --> 08:15.504
Well, my cousin works for this

08:15.506 --> 08:17.372
large accounting firm,
you know,

08:17.374 --> 08:20.208
too large to take Bidexco
on as a client, so,

08:20.210 --> 08:21.609
he helps them out
on the weekends

08:21.611 --> 08:23.677
and they put all
their cash right back

08:23.679 --> 08:25.545
into research so
instead of paying him,

08:25.547 --> 08:27.547
they just issue him stock.

08:27.549 --> 08:29.015
I hate to break
it to your buddy,

08:29.017 --> 08:30.616
but, uh, you should
tell him it's probably

08:30.618 --> 08:32.284
not worth the paper
it's written on.

08:33.152 --> 08:34.418
Well, maybe.

08:35.520 --> 08:38.355
Or maybe he overheard
a researcher talking.

08:38.789 --> 08:39.955
About a breakthrough.

08:40.489 --> 08:42.089
A month before FDA approval.

08:42.490 --> 08:43.722
And since he'd
been doing all this

08:43.957 --> 08:45.857
under the table, he
put all the shares

08:45.859 --> 08:48.125
in this account, in
this trust account,

08:48.127 --> 08:49.593
under a fictitious name.

08:50.127 --> 08:51.460
