refreshes your memory, huh?

43:54.854 --> 43:55.920
What the fuck!

43:56.187 --> 43:57.253
No!

43:57.255 --> 43:58.520
Your memory comin' back now?

43:58.522 --> 44:00.088
Marques Flemmings.

44:00.090 --> 44:01.556
Shit! I told you I don't know!

44:07.195 --> 44:08.595
What the fuck you do?

44:09.663 --> 44:11.530
Oh, man, I'm sorry, my bad.

44:18.370 --> 44:19.669
When he gets into the office,

44:19.671 --> 44:21.370
can you have him
call me, please?

44:21.372 --> 44:22.504
Thank you.

44:23.138 --> 44:24.271
Fucking moron.

44:25.506 --> 44:27.106
Thought you were done
with that shit, man.

44:29.776 --> 44:31.109
I'm trying to stay awake.

44:31.343 --> 44:33.110
-All right.
-Don't judge me.

44:33.112 --> 44:34.978
I am not fucking judging you.

44:34.980 --> 44:36.946
Don't-- Get off your high
horse, you've been...

44:36.948 --> 44:38.681
you've been sober 15 days.

44:38.683 --> 44:40.516
I am not judging you,
Zach, take it easy.

44:44.619 --> 44:45.752
Everything okay?

44:46.687 --> 44:47.853
Peachy.

44:47.855 --> 44:49.287
Anything I can do to help?

44:49.488 --> 44:50.955
This girl's taking a
wrecking ball to my life,

44:50.957 --> 44:52.356
you could help with that.

44:52.358 --> 44:53.857
Well, maybe there's
nothing there.

44:53.859 --> 44:55.692
That was the
private investigator.

44:55.694 --> 44:57.727
She left the house an
hour and a half ago.

44:57.729 --> 44:59.028
She still hasn't come back yet,

44:59.030 --> 45:00.496
she said she was staying in.

45:00.498 --> 45:01.530
Okay, where did
you tell her that

45:01.532 --> 45:02.731
you were going tonight?

45:03.232 --> 45:05.299
What the fuck does that
have to do with anything?

45:05.301 --> 45:06.867
Well, isn't it
obvious that you didn't

45:06.869 --> 45:08.134
tell her the truth either?

45:08.368 --> 45:09.234
And it's not like you're
out fucking around,

45:09.236 --> 45:10.702
that's what I'm saying.

45:10.903 --> 45:12.503
I'm not talking about me,
I'm talking about her.

45:12.505 --> 45:13.871
Are you trying to make
me feel worse here?

45:13.873 --> 45:15.806
-I don't know!
-Whose side are you on?

45:15.808 --> 45:17.541
No, I'm just saying,
maybe look,

45:17.543 --> 45:19.142
maybe this is
naive of me to say,

45:19.144 --> 45:20.376
but isn't it
possible that there's

45:20.378 --> 45:21.710
nothing going on?

45:21.911 --> 45:24.479
Oh, no, not possible.

45:24.481 --> 45:25.813
-Okay.
-Too many holes.

45:25.815 --> 45:26.947
All right.

45:27.348 --> 45:28.581
Too many gaps.

45:30.250 --> 45:31.583
God dammit.

45:32.318 --> 45:34.185
Look, Zach.

45:34.187 --> 45:38.321
I'm not trying to be
your couples' therapist.

45:38.855 --> 45:41.523
All I'm doing is talking to
you as a friend right now.

45:41.525 --> 45:42.891
Okay, well then, talk to me.

45:42.893 --> 45:44.592
I'm telling you
that if you keep going

45:44.594 --> 45:46.293
down this path,
you're always gonna be

45:46.494 --> 45:49.395
questioning and doubting every
little thing that she does.

45:49.397 --> 45:51.263
Until it's gonna get
so bad, she can't

45:51.265 --> 45:52.731
go to the dry cleaners
without you

45:52.733 --> 45:54.733
making a list
in your head

45:54.735 --> 45:56.067
about who she's gonna fuck.

45:56.069 --> 45:56.634
You understand?

46:00.338 --> 46:02.305
If only that
stock went through.

46:03.707 --> 46:05.641
I mean Janie, she's...

46:06.609 --> 46:07.809
she's beautiful.

46:08.410 --> 46:11.078
I mean, I really love her,
we really have a connection.

46:11.279 --> 46:15.281
The only way to manage a
woman like that's happiness,

46:16.716 --> 46:18.349
is with "fuck you" money.

46:22.920 --> 46:26.588
I put every single one of
my clients into that stock.

46:28.891 --> 46:29.957
What?

46:30.591 --> 46:32.592
All of them.
I mean, how many times

46:32.594 --> 46:33.926
do you get to play
the slots knowing

46:34.260 --> 46:36.094
the next pull, three
cherries are gonna come up?

46:36.462 --> 46:39.997
I mean that's a once in
a lifetime opportunity.

46:40.732 --> 46:43.867
Well, listen, man,
you know, sometimes

46:43.869 --> 46:46.069
these things just
work themselves out.

46:46.071 --> 46:49.372
In my line of work, when
you fuck up like that,

46:49.374 --> 46:52.441
it doesn't really
promote career longevity!

46:52.443 --> 46:53.542
Okay.

46:53.876 --> 46:55.109
She's gonna leave me.

46:55.910 --> 46:57.277
Oh, man.

46:57.279 --> 46:58.478
For sure.

47:07.752 --> 47:09.219
Hey.

47:09.221 --> 47:10.286
Jerry.

47:10.620 --> 47:12.020
Go over to Diamond's.

47:12.221 --> 47:13.287
What for?

47:15.623 --> 47:17.757
Okey-doke, we're on our way.

47:17.759 --> 47:18.824
Okay.

47:26.964 --> 47:28.397
Okay, let's do this.

47:28.765 --> 47:29.831
Come on.

47:35.236 --> 47:36.402
Sir.

47:36.404 --> 47:37.669
How can I help you?

47:37.671 --> 47:38.903
Tommy, is he here?

47:38.905 --> 47:40.070
He's under that taxi.

47:44.275 --> 47:45.608
Tommy!

47:45.610 --> 47:46.909
Yeah.

47:48.077 --> 47:49.143
Yeah.

47:49.145 --> 47:50.511
I'm a friend of Paula's.

47:50.513 --> 47:51.612
Okay, she's got
a lot of friends.

47:51.614 --> 47:52.746
Who the fuck are you?

47:52.748 --> 47:53.980
I'm her cousin Eddie.

47:55.816 --> 47:57.982
Oh, fuck. Oh, God, God!

48:01.585 --> 48:03.052
Fuck!

48:04.320 --> 48:07.088
Tell her you're sorry,
you buy her some flowers,

48:07.090 --> 48:08.522
and don't make me come back!

48:39.785 --> 48:40.885
Hank.

48:41.052 --> 48:42.452
I've been expecting you.

48:44.021 --> 48:45.388
What's going on here?

48:45.789 --> 48:47.256
Oh, him, you haven't heard?

48:48.024 --> 48:49.557
Flemmings' nephew got snatched.

48:49.791 --> 48:51.691
He put up a big bank roll
for whoever can find him.

48:51.693 --> 48:53.325
Negro over here
knows where he's at,

48:53.327 --> 48:55.026
but as you can see,
we're having a little bit

48:55.028 --> 48:56.694
of a communication problem.

48:57.062 --> 48:59.029
We're taking a little
break right now.

48:59.031 --> 49:00.230
Yeah, evidently.

49:00.664 --> 49:02.498
Well, we're looking for
his other nephew, Tyrone.

49:02.500 --> 49:04.066
Eddie says you got
an address for us.

49:04.068 --> 49:05.667
Just waitin' for the call.

49:05.669 --> 49:07.535
Friend of mine hangs out
with Tyrone all the time

49:07.537 --> 49:09.370
down at Sullivan's.

49:10.205 --> 49:11.905
Eddie tell you we
agreed to five grand?

49:12.506 --> 49:13.973
You get this when
I get the address.

49:14.541 --> 49:15.807
Sure.

49:15.809 --> 49:17.141
No problem.

49:17.143 --> 49:19.243
Have a drink,
shouldn't be long.

49:19.811 --> 49:20.877
All right.

49:25.649 --> 49:26.782
Guys!

49:27.583 --> 49:29.216
Come here.

49:29.218 --> 49:30.383
Come here.

49:35.922 --> 49:37.389
So that was Eddie.

49:38.023 --> 49:40.724
He said everything on
his end is going forward.

49:42.059 --> 49:43.092
And?

49:43.094 --> 49:44.226
And that's it.

49:44.228 --> 49:45.894
Now we just sit, and we wait.

49:45.896 --> 49:47.562
Sit and wait, wonderful.

49:47.564 --> 49:49.163
Well, did he give you
any idea how much

49:49.165 --> 49:50.531
longer it'd be?

49:50.533 --> 49:51.965
Shut up, Noah!

49:52.199 --> 49:53.933
Look, let's just take shifts
watching him, all right?

49:53.935 --> 49:55.401
We'll switch out
every two hours.

49:55.403 --> 49:57.236
This way
we can get some sleep.

49:57.238 --> 49:58.537
-Yeah, all right.
-Okay, all right.

49:58.539 --> 49:59.671
I'll go first.

49:59.673 --> 50:00.872
You sure?

50:00.874 --> 50:01.939
Yeah.

50:08.612 --> 50:09.945
Did I ever tell
you guys how I got

50:09.947 --> 50:11.613
this scar on my ear?

50:11.615 --> 50:13.247
-Uh-uh.
-You haven't heard that?

50:13.249 --> 50:14.281
Nope.

50:14.283 --> 50:15.782
I thought I told that to ya.

50:15.949 --> 50:17.249
Crazy story.

50:17.850 --> 50:20.284
My older brother, who
was pursuing a career

50:20.286 --> 50:21.718
in law enforcement,
decided to go

50:21.720 --> 50:23.252
in a different direction,
and was dealing

50:23.254 --> 50:25.420
eight balls that were
one-third product,

50:25.422 --> 50:26.954
two-thirds baking soda.

50:27.588 --> 50:29.388
<i> I'm home with chicken pox,
 when, you know,</i>

50:29.390 --> 50:30.756
<i> one of his disgruntled
 clients decided</i>

50:30.758 --> 50:32.190
<i> to pay a house visit.</i>

50:33.859 --> 50:35.693
<i> So, he wanted to know
 where my brother was,</i>

50:35.695 --> 50:37.594
<i> and how a household
 baking ingredient</i>

50:37.596 --> 50:39.262
<i> ended up inside the bag.</i>

50:40.464 --> 50:41.931
<i> I told him I don't know,
 and that</i>

50:41.933 --> 50:43.632
<i> my chicken pox was contagious.</i>

50:44.433 --> 50:46.267
<i> He apparently wasn't
 pleased with that answer.</i>

50:47.068 --> 50:49.102
<i> Meanwhile, this kid
 Isaac was living</i>

50:49.104 --> 50:50.770
<i> in the apartment downstairs.</i>

50:52.873 --> 50:54.406
<i> On this day,
 he decides to come home</i>

50:54.408 --> 50:56.340
<i> a little earlier than
 his mother expected.</i>

50:59.143 --> 51:02.444
<i>Finds her home a little earlier
 than he expected as well.</i>

51:05.314 --> 51:06.681
<i> So he goes into the
 kitchen, and instead of</i>

51:06.948 --> 51:08.581
<i> looking in the
 refrigerator for his usual,</i>

51:08.583 --> 51:10.816
<i> you know, after-school treat,
 he helps himself</i>

51:10.818 --> 51:13.351
<i> to his father's
 sawed-off shotgun.</i>

51:14.920 --> 51:17.954
<i> Meanwhile, my situation
 upstairs was deteriorating.</i>

51:19.423 --> 51:21.689
<i> This asshole was
 gonna cut my ear off.</i>

51:33.600 --> 51:35.534
<i> It was nothing short
 of divine intervention.</i>

51:37.136 --> 51:38.936
<i> I'm telling you, man, if it
 wasn't for this kid Isaac,</i>

51:38.938 --> 51:40.870
<i> the guy would've taken
 my ear clean off.</i>

51:43.607 --> 51:44.873
It was a fucking miracle.

51:45.975 --> 51:47.342
--What the fuck?

51:49.245 --> 51:50.744
You've got a gun, get me.

52:05.590 --> 52:06.690
Fuck.

52:07.091 --> 52:08.658
What the fuck'd you
do that for, Jerry?

52:09.626 --> 52:10.926
Say hi to Isaac.

52:12.628 --> 52:13.761
Hi, Isaac.

52:14.162 --> 52:15.462
What are the odds of that?

52:15.464 --> 52:16.563
I don't know.

52:30.477 --> 52:31.577
Hey, buddy.

52:32.946 --> 52:34.179
You look like shit.

52:40.150 --> 52:41.283
Hello?

52:41.285 --> 52:44.152
<i> Yo, Tyrone
 is hangin' with his ho at
 Second Side Apartments.</i>

52:44.154 --> 52:45.153
<i> Second floor on the left.</i>

52:45.155 --> 52:46.087
Thanks.

52:48.390 --> 52:49.556
We're good.

52:49.558 --> 52:50.723
We're good!

52:50.725 --> 52:51.857
You good?

52:52.391 --> 52:53.958
Let's get the fuck outta here.

53:10.708 --> 53:12.308
You ever fire one of those?

53:14.744 --> 53:16.010
What?

53:16.012 --> 53:17.311
Gun.

53:18.513 --> 53:19.713
Call me crazy.

53:20.414 --> 53:22.214
You don't seem like the type.

53:23.015 --> 53:24.982
Not that you couldn't
if you had to.

53:24.984 --> 53:26.783
Well, let's not give
me a reason to have to.

53:27.417 --> 53:30.452
Hey, I'm on board with that.

53:32.822 --> 53:35.890
You know where I come
from, if somebody

53:35.892 --> 53:37.892
asks you to put some
iron in the back

53:37.894 --> 53:40.294
of somebody's head
that you never met,

53:41.262 --> 53:42.428
you just do it.

53:43.496 --> 53:45.162
No questions asked.

53:47.899 --> 53:50.700
When you was growin' up,
did your pops

53:50.702 --> 53:54.503
ever tell you to do
uncomfortable shit

53:54.505 --> 53:56.338
because it made you
build character?

53:56.340 --> 53:57.405
All the time.

53:57.407 --> 53:59.073
My pops, too.

53:59.541 --> 54:00.841
You know,

54:01.108 --> 54:03.008
he was a big proponent
of character building.

54:04.610 --> 54:06.377
And me, you know, I
was like the oldest,

54:06.379 --> 54:09.646
so he decided he wanted
to get me started early.

54:10.381 --> 54:12.448
Check it out, he sent
me over to this house.

54:12.782 --> 54:16.484
With nothing but a
flare and some matches.

54:17.018 --> 54:19.386
By the time the
fire truck showed up,

54:19.388 --> 54:21.221
there wasn't nothing
left but ashes.

54:21.223 --> 54:22.488
Now I didn't find out
'til I saw

54:22.755 --> 54:25.223
in the paper the next
morning, that there was

54:25.225 --> 54:26.924
a family of four inside.

54:28.960 --> 54:30.327
None of which made it out.

54:32.063 --> 54:33.663
Nigga, I was 13.

54:37.100 --> 54:41.435
As you can imagine,
sucked all the fun

54:41.437 --> 54:43.336
right out of my childhood.

54:50.810 --> 54:52.210
You ever wonder what
your life would be like

54:52.212 --> 54:53.878
if you chose a different path?

54:54.546 --> 54:55.913
You mean doing
something other than

54:55.915 --> 54:57.848
going into the family business?

55:02.452 --> 55:04.553
Only every day.

55:27.173 --> 55:28.472
Hey, Noah, are you awake?

55:31.342 --> 55:32.575
Yeah.

55:33.410 --> 55:36.578
That cow on the window is
really freaking me out.

55:38.782 --> 55:40.414
Oh, shit, yeah.

55:40.948 --> 55:43.215
-That's some freaky shit, man.
-Christ Almighty.

55:47.653 --> 55:50.488
Hey, Noah, um,
there's something

55:50.490 --> 55:52.322
I kinda want to
talk to you about.

55:54.658 --> 55:56.025
Yeah, what is it?

55:57.327 --> 55:58.960
Well, you know how
in AA there's that

55:58.962 --> 56:03.330
whole thing about, you know,
making amends, whatever,

56:03.332 --> 56:05.265
with people that you've
hurt in the past?

56:06.166 --> 56:07.266
Mm-hm.

56:07.500 --> 56:09.934
You know Zach
and Matthew and I,

56:10.335 --> 56:12.936
you know back in
the day we, we were

56:12.938 --> 56:15.738
pretty relentless
about torturing you.

56:17.173 --> 56:18.706
Warren, I was the
only kid in school

56:18.708 --> 56:20.841
who knew how to
use the word binary

56:20.843 --> 56:22.642
in a sentence, that pretty much

56:22.644 --> 56:25.011
warranted open season on me.

56:25.979 --> 56:28.380
I mean, Noah, we really
pulled some shit on you.

56:30.316 --> 56:31.582
Yeah, well.

56:33.151 --> 56:36.553
What doesn't kill you
makes you stronger.

56:37.021 --> 56:38.121
Right?

56:38.123 --> 56:39.288
Yeah.

56:39.290 --> 56:40.389
Well.

56:41.124 --> 56:42.891
I just wanted you to
know that, you know,

56:42.893 --> 56:47.629
I feel bad about it and,
uh, and I'm sorry.

56:50.532 --> 56:51.765
All right.

57:01.641 --> 57:05.777
Half, a million, dollars.

57:11.316 --> 57:12.582
That's my offer.

57:14.851 --> 57:18.119
All you got to do is un-cuff me,

57:18.587 --> 57:20.887
and let me walk out
that door unchecked.

57:22.723 --> 57:23.923
I can't do that.

57:25.225 --> 57:29.795
500K that you get to keep.

57:30.663 --> 57:31.796
For yourself.

57:33.899 --> 57:35.966
My brother, you
better think hard.

57:36.600 --> 57:39.468
My offer ain't just gonna
hang out there in the ether.

57:39.769 --> 57:41.269
Before sunup one of
you's gonna realize,

57:41.536 --> 57:44.470
that you ain't got the
stomach for this kinda thing.

57:45.371 --> 57:46.671
Now take the dough.

58:24.108 --> 58:25.708
Hey, Bryce, man, I...

58:28.912 --> 58:30.178
Fuck!

58:35.050 --> 58:36.316
Fuck! Fuck!

58:53.166 --> 58:55.333
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

59:10.348 --> 59:11.581
Oh!

59:12.749 --> 59:14.583
Jesus Christ, you scared
the shit outta me!

59:14.585 --> 59:15.650
Fuck are you doing?

59:15.652 --> 59:16.984
I'm planning my great escape.

59:16.986 --> 59:18.185
What the fuck
does it look like?

59:18.986 --> 59:20.486
Oh, it stinks!

59:20.488 --> 59:22.154
Wanna wipe my ass?
You look eager!

59:26.926 --> 59:28.626
-Paula.
-Hey, Eddie.

59:28.628 --> 59:29.994
How are ya?

59:29.996 --> 59:31.161
A couple guys showed up,
said that, uh,

59:31.163 --> 59:32.328
they had a meeting with you so

59:32.330 --> 59:33.762
I sat them at your table.

59:33.764 --> 59:35.363
-Oh.
-They're drinking Diet Cokes.

59:35.365 --> 59:36.597
Put it on my tab.

59:36.599 --> 59:37.898
-Eddie.
-Yeah?

59:38.366 --> 59:39.899
-Thank you.
-For what?

59:40.867 --> 59:42.100
Thank you.

59:44.503 --> 59:45.803
Hey.
How are you?

59:45.805 --> 59:47.004
Hey, Eddie.
Good to see ya.

59:47.006 --> 59:48.205
-How you doin'?
-Good.

59:48.207 --> 59:49.339
Take care.

59:49.341 --> 59:51.207
Gentlemen.
Traffic, sorry.

59:51.209 --> 59:53.209
Agent Reichert.

59:53.211 --> 59:54.677
-Hey.
-What happened?

59:54.679 --> 59:56.145
-Eh, line of duty.
-Ah.

59:56.147 --> 59:58.647
This is my partner,
Agent Santos.

59:58.649 --> 01:00:00.215
-How do you do?
- Sir.

01:00:00.217 --> 01:00:01.382
-Wanna talk?
-Yeah.

01:00:01.384 --> 01:00:02.449
Let's do it.

01:00:02.883 --> 01:00:04.016
You look good, Eddie.

01:00:04.018 --> 01:00:05.684
Ah, thanks, how's the wife?

01:00:05.686 --> 01:00:07.318
Well, you know how it is.

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:09.553
She ain't getting any younger
or any thinner.

01:00:10.856 --> 01:00:11.988
Mr. Lovato.

01:00:11.990 --> 01:00:13.456
Eddie, please.

01:00:13.458 --> 01:00:15.291
Mr. Lovato, as you
may have already heard,

01:00:15.293 --> 01:00:16.725
Demetrius Flemmings'
nephew, Marques

01:00:16.727 --> 01:00:18.359
was kidnapped yesterday.

01:00:18.361 --> 01:00:19.526
You know about this?

01:00:20.294 --> 01:00:21.594
I do not.

01:00:21.795 --> 01:00:23.295
Well, the two of us
know that the two of you

01:00:23.297 --> 01:00:24.529
have past issues.

01:00:24.531 --> 01:00:25.530
I have?

01:00:25.532 --> 01:00:27.798
Sorry Eddie, we have to ask.

01:00:28.533 --> 01:00:30.567
Anything you can give
us will be a big help.

01:00:31.702 --> 01:00:34.236
Sound and fury,
signifying nothing.

01:00:34.238 --> 01:00:35.437
Hmm?

01:00:36.005 --> 01:00:37.138
<i>It's a line from Macbeth,
have you ever seen it?</i>

01:00:37.140 --> 01:00:38.539
-No.
-No.

01:00:38.541 --> 01:00:40.040
Oh, it's my favorite play.

01:00:40.042 --> 01:00:41.241
I love it.

01:00:41.575 --> 01:00:43.375
I saw it on Broadway
with Patrick Stewart.

01:00:43.709 --> 01:00:45.843
<i>He's the bald guy from
 Star Trek, remember?</i>

01:00:45.845 --> 01:00:47.411
Yeah, he's good.

01:00:47.413 --> 01:00:49.813
